The paper deals with algorithms for computing abelian runs, which are a type of substring in a given word. This falls under the category of string algorithms, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper involve computational complexity and randomness, which are also topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial aspects, such as Parikh vectors and abelian periods, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves information theory, as it discusses the norm of Parikh vectors, which is a measure of information content (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves formal languages, as it deals with substrings and periods in words, which are topics in formal language theory (cs.FL).
